events.name: Portland Trail Blazers at Indiana Pacers

headlines.description: — Oshae Brissett scored 24 points, Justin Anderson had 18 and the Indiana Pacers cruised past the Portland Trail Blazers 129-98 Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Brissett leads Pacers past Trail Blazers 129-98

headlines.description: — Desmond Bane had 24 points and the Memphis Grizzlies overcame the absence of star Ja Morant with balanced scoring in a 122-98 victory over the NBA-worst Houston Rockets on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bane has 24 points, Grizzlies rout Rockets without Morant

events.name: New Orleans Pelicans at Atlanta Hawks

headlines.description: — Jonas Valanciunas had 26 points and 12 rebounds, CJ McCollum added 25 points, and the New Orleans Pelicans beat the Atlanta Hawks 117-112 on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Valanciunas, McCollum power Pelicans past Hawks 117-112

events.name: Oklahoma City Thunder at Orlando Magic

headlines.description: — Wendell Carter Jr. scored 10 of his career-high 30 points in the fourth quarter and the Orlando Magic handed the Oklahoma City Thunder their ninth straight loss with a 90-85 victory Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Carter, Magic hand Thunder 9th straight loss, 90-85

events.name: Utah Jazz at New York Knicks

headlines.description: — Donovan Mitchell scored 36 points and the Utah Jazz finished strong to start their road trip, beating the New York Knicks 108-93 on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Mitchell scores 36 points, Jazz beat Knicks to open trip

headlines.description: — Jaylen Brown and Jayson Tatum each scored 30 points and the sizzling Boston Celtics stymied reigning MVP Nikola Jokic on their way to routing the Denver Nuggets 124-104 Sunday night.
— The 76ers acquired James Harden to score big baskets when the game is on the line.
headlines.shortLinkText: Raptors win 6th straight road game, top 76ers 93-88

events.name: San Antonio Spurs at Golden State Warriors

headlines.description: — Keldon Johnson scored off a rebound of a missed free throw with three-tenths of a second left to give the San Antonio Spurs a 110-108 victory over the Golden State Warriors on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Johnson scores off missed FT, Spurs beat Curry-less Warriors
